725087f-a.text:
Twentieth Ave., west of 33rd Street, showing at the left a one story garage located at the Southwest Corner of 31st Street and Twentieth Avenue. At the right is the property of the Astoria Light, Heat and Power Company.
May 1929.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.

725088f-b.text:
Twentieth Ave., south side, between 35th (right) and 33rd Street (left) and 33rd Street (left) showing the George Kouwenhoven farmhouse. This is a rear view; the house faces on Old Bowery Road. It was demolished in May 1929. This is a set of three views. See Twentieth Road for more data.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection. Views 1,2&3.
